    "plan_content": "The plan is ready. Here's a summary of what will be done — **two additions to `common/chat.cpp` only**, no other files touched:\n\n---\n\n### Change 1 — New static handler function (insert before line 1634)\n\nAdd `common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3()` between `common_chat_extra_context()` and `common_chat_try_specialized_template()`. It:\n- Iterates `inputs.messages`, buffering any `system` message in `pending_system`\n- Prepends `tmpl.bos_token()` (`<s>`) once before the first user turn\n- Wraps user turns as `[INST] {content} [/INST]`, injecting the system message as `[INST] {system}\\n{content} [/INST]` on the first user turn\n- Appends assistant turns as ` {content}</s>`\n- Sets `data.format = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY` and returns\n\n### Change 2 — Detection block (insert inside `common_chat_try_specialized_template()`, after the Ministral block)\n\n```cpp\nif (src.find(\"[INST]\") != std::string::npos && src.find(\"[/INST]\") != std::string::npos &&\n    src.find(\"[SYSTEM_PROMPT]\") == std::string::npos) {\n    LOG_DBG(\"Using specialized template: Mistral Instruct v3\\n\");\n    return common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(tmpl, params);\n}\n```\n\nPlaced after the Ministral check (so the more-specific `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]`-based detection fires first) and before the GPT-OSS check.",
